  "local_port": 34428,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What can I include in areas of interests in my resume?",
  "response": "Including \"Areas of Interest\" in your resume can provide additional insight into your personality, passions, and potential cultural fit within a company. However, it\u2019s important to keep this section professional and relevant. Here are some ideas for what you can include:\n\n### 1. **Professional Interests**\n   - Industry-specific topics (e.g., artificial intelligence, renewable energy, digital marketing)\n   - Emerging technologies (e.g., blockchain, machine learning, IoT)\n   - Professional development (e.g., leadership, project management, public speaking)\n\n### 2. **Hobbies and Creative Pursuits**\n   - Creative activities (e.g., photography, graphic design, blogging)\n   - Writing or editing (e.g., technical writing, creative writing)\n   - Arts and crafts (e.g., painting, woodworking, DIY projects)\n\n### 3. **Community and Social Interests**\n   - Volunteering or community service (e.g., mentoring, fundraising, local charities)\n   - Social causes (e.g., environmental sustainability, social justice, education)\n   - Non-profits or advocacy groups\n\n### 4. **Physical and Outdoor Activities**\n   - Sports or fitness (e.g., running, yoga, cycling)\n   - Outdoor activities (e.g., hiking, camping, gardening)\n   - Team sports (e.g., soccer, basketball, volleyball)\n\n### 5. **Learning and Intellectual Interests**\n   - Reading (e.g., non-fiction, industry-related books, biographies)\n   - Research or academic interests (e.g., history, psychology, economics)\n   - Online courses or certifications (e.g., Coursera, Udemy)\n\n### 6. **Cultural Interests**\n   - Music (e.g., playing an instrument, attending concerts)\n   - Travel and cultural exploration\n   - Film or theater (e.g., independent films, Broadway shows)\n\n### 7. **Technical or Niche Interests**\n   - Coding or software development (e.g., open-source projects, hackathons)\n   - Gaming (e.g., strategy games, game design)\n   - DIY tech projects (e.g., robotics, electronics)\n\n### 8. **Networking and Professional Organizations**\n   - Membership in professional associations (e.g., IEEE, AMA)\n   - Alumni groups or networking clubs\n   - Conferences or industry events attended\n\n### Tips for Including Areas of Interest:\n   - **Be selective:** Choose interests that align with the job or company culture.\n   - **Keep it concise:** Limit the section to 3\u20135 interests.\n   - **Show relevance:** Highlight hobbies or interests that demonstrate transferable skills (e.g., teamwork, creativity, problem-solving).\n   - **Avoid controversial topics:** Stay away from polarizing or overly personal interests.\n   - **Tailor it:** Customize this section for each job application to make it more impactful.\n\nExample:\n**Areas of Interest:** Data visualization, sustainable living, mentoring young professionals, hiking, and attending tech meetups.\n\nThis section can serve as a conversation starter during interviews and help you stand out as a well-rounded candidate.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
